{
  "text": "In order to prove that all supercyclicity criteria are equivalent to the supercyclicity of T \u00a9 T, we adapt some ideas of Bes and Peris [CITATION_1] the Universality Criterion for some (n*) and {A nt }* g N C K \\ {0}. That is, T satisfies the Supercyclicity Criterion. D Supercyclic operators have been mainly studied in the context of (complex) Banach spaces. Therefore it was natural to state the criteria in the Banach setting having in mind the concrete applications of these criteria. We shall show the equivalence of two supercyclicity criteria given by Feldman, Miller and Miller in [CITATION_2] to the Supercyclicity Criterion. PROOF: It is obvious that any operator satisfying the Supercyclicity Criterion also satisfies the criteria of (b) and (c). We are done if we show the supercyclicity of T (B T for any operator T satisfying (b) or (c). We shall prove this for the Outer Criterion (b) since the other case is analogous.",
